10/08/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Some 1,000 US military personnel and civilian employees will be in Romania between August 17th and October 22nd for a joint military drill with Bulgarian and Romanian solders, the US Embassy in Bucharest announced on Thursday (August 9th). 
The embassy added that soldiers, airmen and sailors are working together now with their Romanian counterparts to set up the exercise, which includes training in small calibre weapons firing, live fire exercises, situational training exercises and first aid. 
(US embassy press release - 09/08/07)
